 (She/Her)', 'Accessibility program innovation and strategy architect, sought-after writing and public speaking expert with a history of successfully architecting strategic global accessibility programs in a Fortune 200 environment. My expertise includes deploying corporate policies, accessible digital property design and remediation using LEAN and AGILE software development techniques, analytics, and maturity modelling.

Multi-dimensional with a unique skillset and career background spanning computer science, law, and business, alongside professional certifications in ADA Coordination and Accessibility Professional Core Competencies, allowing for a complete 360-degree view of issues surrounding accessibility.

Member of the International Associate of Accessibility Professionals Global Leadership Council and Certification committee, Information Tecnhology Industry Council VPAT subcommittee and W3C Silver and Maturity Model committees.

Prolific writer and blogger on disability and accessibility topics, with over 180 published articles on medium.com (https://medium.com/@sheribyrnehaber), reaching up to 500,000 readers. Featured top writer in the diversity, design, accessibility, and equity categories. Winner of the 2020 Medium UX Collective Author of the Year award.

